The Police have confirmed that they are aware of a suspected syndicate allegedly operating in the city and that Polokwane Police Station was instructed to intensify patrols in the area.
Provincial Police Communications Head, Motlafela Mojapelo confirmed that they recently received reports of an alleged syndicate, targeting motorists by distracting them and then stealing from their vehicles.
The warning trending on social media indicates that the suspected syndicate allegedly operates in Landdros MarÃ©, Devenish and Market streets.
The modus operandi entails a woman approaching the driver of a vehicle pretending to ask directions to the offices of the South Africa Social Security Agency.
While the driver is being distracted her male accomplice would allegedly take the opportunity to steal valuable items from the vehicle.
